<subSubSection id="ED3C23FDAAE4F6485C14025D7C8FEA8E" lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="030931081ED97C487B805AAC31BDD65B" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="38F167CFBCD7C0F3B3CE004D70F6B256" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
In 2005 the first author viewed the type collection of 
<taxonomicName id="6CDF39AD00F2438DD619E4A13C465488" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruprechtii">
<emphasis id="AEBE922D8275B3E74EC8AD7C7C1E63C7" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa ruprechtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at W and (regrettably) annotated it as &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="0F87CEB4E2F0BD50802255083B640689" authorityName="Hitchc. Contr. U. S. Natl. Herb. 17 (3): 374" authorityYear="1913" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orizabensis">
<emphasis id="ABF764F3C1DEE2DBCFC72BEE04DED029" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa orizabensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hitchc.?&quot; At that time there was no notation on this specimens indicating it was the type of 
<taxonomicName id="5875573B515F7723B65A457FAACE6F26" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruprechtii">
<emphasis id="2C7B460A3E2696E4A302732C469D7554" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa ruprechtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Subsequent searches for the type at W by Bruno 
<normalizedToken id="DE04EF224E0DB8F38BF65526A6BA0907" originalValue="Wallnöfer">Wallnoefer</normalizedToken>
, and other curators where 
<emphasis id="AB2073257EFD47B6E0772669C298D445" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">C. Heller</emphasis>
material from Mexico might exist (IB, K, LE, WU), did not relocate this collection until 2011. Thanks to the attentive eyes of Lia Pignotti (W), the type was rediscovered at W in the 
<taxonomicName id="BADF7CD6D088D0A7182E8217EDB5CCA3" authorityName="Hitchc. Contr. U. S. Natl. Herb. 17 (3): 374" authorityYear="1913" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orizabensis">
<emphasis id="4EEA8AF42F448000B488042B1643D636" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa orizabensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
folder. The type was originally determined as 
<taxonomicName id="FD62639C3E5AEAADF2A05981A8E505E2" authorityName="L., Sp. Pl. 1: 68" authorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="annua">
<emphasis id="3395BDC2B25F8324552E251B5B62B747" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa annua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. That epithet and author were then crossed out and replaced by 
<taxonomicName id="2A2955247C8E63ACE5D903ECE5F816EF" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flexuosa">
<emphasis id="FE43123C1F16D51C4921330DC020A469" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa flexuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Muhl. (
<figureCitation id="F8A49EEE9305149EB8754A19DE2BA603" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Poa ruprechtii Peyr. Photo of holotype collection (Heller 312)." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10151" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
; see discussion of 
<taxonomicName id="BF039B49CF2BFC3F25A0015C642A84C6" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flexuosa">
<emphasis id="4F1C7EC090051027B859FE1D59C53975" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa flexuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName id="300BE94332C641F1ABE9488AEDE7AAA8" authorityName="Soreng &amp; P. M. Peterson" authorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="palmeri">
<emphasis id="B3B6AA1446D0B42FCAC245575CC995B4" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa palmeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Heller collected on the north slopes of 
<normalizedToken id="8ED63E07DD432FBAE00F73CC7F2BE82F" originalValue="Volcán">Volcan</normalizedToken>
Toluca between August 10-14, 1846, near Hacienda Cocustepec above the &quot;small hamlets San Buenaventura and Cacalomacan&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="07A598EED1B460BC614AB0D35B1973EE" author="Heller, KB" journalOrPublisher="Australian Systematic Botany" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refId="B21" refString="Heller, KB, Rugeley, T, 2007. Alone in Mexico: the astonishing travels of Karl Heller 1845-1848. University of Alabama Press." title="Alone in Mexico: the astonishing travels of Karl Heller 1845 - 1848. University of Alabama Press." year="2007">Heller and Rugeley 2007</bibRefCitation>
; an English translation of 
<normalizedToken id="13E8EAC9708E810B2A7E9258A9D49647" originalValue="Heller’s">Heller's</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="DF7ED5FE292039FC3504EC0A00515974" originalValue="travel’s">travel's</normalizedToken>
in Mexico, originally published in German). The type locality for 
<taxonomicName id="C5F4555E0FD6024765E6CEA374C2E065" authorityName="Swallen" authorityYear="1950" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sharpii">
<emphasis id="149490B657CAA161F2191E8574578802" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa sharpii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, &quot;El Puerto, 7700 ft&quot; in Veracruz, is somewhere above the city of Orizaba on the southeast side of 
<normalizedToken id="2C29BDCDEE6AFAA86BCE30F6165811AC" originalValue="Volcán">Volcan</normalizedToken>
Orizaba. The species should also be searched for on or about the slopes of 
<normalizedToken id="0EDCD54A19C6441268E655A835129BDE" originalValue="Volcán">Volcan</normalizedToken>
Orizaba in Puebla.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8867016601FC6E236A7045D5168AA9B2" lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
Specimens previously identified as &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="6D1130C751BC4AB1B8D95C223C81ED5E" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruprechtii">
<emphasis id="F5BBEAFC5D8B1DC95C4809112F8A8EF0" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa ruprechtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; from Coahuila and Nuevo 
<normalizedToken id="E19E4298EF6E905A81FB7B1285D72F4E" originalValue="León">Leon</normalizedToken>
, by 
<bibRefCitation id="B14E3E5EF750F9008094196B5B130B26" author="Hitchcock, AS" journalOrPublisher="Australian Systematic Botany" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refId="B25" refString="Hitchcock, AS, 1913. Mexican grasses in the United States National Herbarium. Contributions from the United States National Herbarium 17(3): 181-389." title="Mexican grasses in the United States National Herbarium. Contributions from the United States National Herbarium 17 (3): 181 - 389." year="1913">Hitchcock (1913)</bibRefCitation>
and others, belong to 
<taxonomicName id="1CF7F7CA41DCAB1049E10D4988688212" authorityName="Soreng &amp; P. M. Peterson" authorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="palmeri">
<emphasis id="6FB8E86B6B63E141586CF99F54E180C5" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa palmeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see discussion under that species). 
<bibRefCitation id="6AF0DA2F0453BB6DD92EBD61AE8E9923" author="Espejo Serna, A" journalOrPublisher="Euphytica" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refId="B12" refString="Espejo Serna, A, Lopez-Ferrari, AR, Valdes-Reyna, J, 2000. Poaceae.In: A. Espejo Serna A, Lopez-Ferrari AR (Eds) Las Monocotiledoneas Mexicanas: una Sinopsis Floristica, Partes IX-XI. Consejo Nacional de la Flora de Mexico, A.C., Universidad Autonoma Metropolitana-Iztapalapa, and Comision Nacional para el Conocimiento y uso de la Biodiversidad, Mexico, D.F. 10: 8-236." title="Poaceae. In: A. Espejo Serna A, Lopez-Ferrari AR (Eds) Las Monocotiledoneas Mexicanas: una Sinopsis Floristica, Partes IX-XI. Consejo Nacional de la Flora de Mexico, A. C., Universidad Autonoma Metropolitana-Iztapalapa, and Comision Nacional para el Conocimiento y uso de la Biodiversidad, Mexico, D. F. 10: 8 - 236." year="2000">Espejo Serna et al. (2000)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="B627B6198861D276C97C6341B5E6B28A" author="Davila Aranda, P" journalOrPublisher="Euphytica" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refId="B11" refString="Davila Aranda, P, Mejia-Saules, MT, Gomez-Sanchez, M, Valdes-Reyna, J, Ortiz, JJ, Morin, C, Castrejon, J, Ocampo, A, 2006. Catalogo de las Gramineas de Mexico. i-xii, 1-671 + errata." title="Catalogo de las Gramineas de Mexico. i-xii, 1 - 671 + errata." year="2006">
<normalizedToken id="D7AA79F84668B5EA1B686665E4FFEB51" originalValue="Dávila">Davila</normalizedToken>
Aranda et al. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
accepted 
<taxonomicName id="243EFEC801E8ED4D9FEF0416108ED110" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruprechtii">
<emphasis id="2D984F1986A195B34F136BB72F2E0FAB" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa ruprechtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.l. and 
<taxonomicName id="F3C5A04B2ED990EC80C81D55EBBE6C4A" authorityName="Swallen" authorityYear="1950" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sharpii">
<emphasis id="EFBA85E0BC69CBC0CB46836CE78A5016" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa sharpii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="FE6B163A33C4BA9BF8B9EF02C6D34647" author="Beetle, AA" journalOrPublisher="Naturaliste Canadien" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="173 - 180" refId="B6" refString="Beetle, AA, 1987. Las Gramineas de Mexico, Tomo II: 1-344. Secretaria de Agricultura y Recursos Hidraulicos: COTECOCA, Mexico.Boivin B, Loeve, D (1960) Poa agassizensis, a new prairie bluegrass. Naturaliste Canadien 87: 173 - 180" title="Las Gramineas de Mexico, Tomo II: 1 - 344. Secretaria de Agricultura y Recursos Hidraulicos: COTECOCA, Mexico. Boivin B, Loeve, D (1960) Poa agassizensis, a new prairie bluegrass." volume="87" year="1987">Beetle (1987)</bibRefCitation>
attempted to resolve the disposition of the northern plants by placing them in 
<taxonomicName id="67B9EDCECC62359834F4B6DBEDD237FA" authorityName="Vasey" authorityYear="1893" baseAuthorityName="Hook." class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nervosa">
<emphasis id="E5357B82DFA1FDD37E2B226B50439F0C" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa nervosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hook.) Vasey. References to the name and material of 
<taxonomicName id="AF8FBBE21FC76B2ABE28D96062EFB796" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruprechtii">
<emphasis id="B844E971757FCCEC95257928C3DE1CFD" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa ruprechtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.l. were simply left out of the volume of 
<normalizedToken id="0A766A3751AF93493A39CFE9B7090588" originalValue="Beetle’s">Beetle's</normalizedToken>
treatises on the grasses of Mexico that included 
<taxonomicName id="D6ACE0BEB52ED682CF8BAE13282E1D03" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9CAE32272E70B32433BF96BC2A1CE6C4" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="B18BC9D28D4B9858B1DD922ADFA5B2D6" author="Manrique de Skendzic, E" journalOrPublisher="Australian Systematic Botany" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refId="B29" refString="Manrique de Skendzic, E, 1999. Poa L. In: Beetle AA, Villegas-Duran G, Bolanos-Medina A, Miranda-Sanchez JA, Aragon-Melchor L, Vergara-Batalla MA, Chimal Hernandez A, Castillo-Badillo MM, Galvan-Garcia OM, Villalpando-Prieto JL, Lizama-Manrique M, Valdes-Reyna J, Manrique-de Skendzic E, Rodriguez-Rodriguez AM (Eds) Las Gramineas de Mexico, Tomo V. Secretaria de Agricultura, Ganaderia y Desarrollo Rural, Distrito Federal, Mexico." title="Poa L. In: Beetle AA, Villegas-Duran G, Bolanos-Medina A, Miranda-Sanchez JA, Aragon-Melchor L, Vergara-Batalla MA, Chimal Hernandez A, Castillo-Badillo MM, Galvan-Garcia OM, Villalpando-Prieto JL, Lizama-Manrique M, Valdes-Reyna J, Manrique-de Skendzic E, Rodriguez-Rodriguez AM (Eds) Las Gramineas de Mexico, Tomo V. Secretaria de Agricultura, Ganaderia y Desarrollo Rural, Distrito Federal, Mexico." year="1999">Manrique-Skendzic 1999</bibRefCitation>
). The description of this species given here is based on the material from Mexico cited above. The name 
<taxonomicName id="3C2049152EF17E8EF5D8712670DE57CD" authorityName="Swallen" authorityYear="1950" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="venosa">
<emphasis id="3C9135BA32101B00C4F1789AF3FF31A3" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa venosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Swallen has been applied to this taxon in Guatemala, the type of which is a fairly robust specimen of the species, with lemmas quite hairy between the veins. However, other specimens from Guatemala to which that name has been applied are quite variable and approach 
<taxonomicName id="7F3D55879DAEF68DBDE3B46F8CF7C55C" authorityName="Hitchc. Contr. U. S. Natl. Herb. 17 (3): 374" authorityYear="1913" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orizabensis">
<emphasis id="257B430EF84BE6829EAD10BA0DFBFC53" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa orizabensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="5C15EF66F3B91EC14734E89A166058D0" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruprechtii">
<emphasis id="ED5EB848E2F6377E7EBAC44A1083DA86" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa ruprechtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="25A8D9885DD369774BEA405171999A26" authorityName="Hitchc. Contr. U. S. Natl. Herb. 17 (3): 374" authorityYear="1913" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orizabensis">
<emphasis id="30E53C8012CAA3F2F81DD81A90445375" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Poa orizabensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having lemmas that are distinctly short villous on the keel and lateral nerves and sometimes puberulent between the nerves, versus lemmas that are glabrous or very sparsely puberulent on the base of keel and sometimes the marginal vein, and glabrous elsewhere. Also the glumes 
<pageBreakToken id="7574EB3BFB417E2949964CC7EA9D525B" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" start="start">in</pageBreakToken>
<taxonomicName id="19331303214BF455DC8FCC8FBBEBB4D4" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruprechtii">
<emphasis id="4F9E1074CF16A76C90BC7D07736EAEBD" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Poa ruprechtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are narrower in proportion to their length, and the spikelets are less compact than in 
<taxonomicName id="94150AB43CAE87FCA152E70DBEB75A3E" authorityName="Hitchc. Contr. U. S. Natl. Herb. 17 (3): 374" authorityYear="1913" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orizabensis">
<emphasis id="E1BA85B676DD13AE7B71AB208F930E90" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Poa orizabensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, a few specimens display intermediate combinations of characteristics in Mexico (see notes on 
<taxonomicName id="52EC327DAD057A37217FFFF114C9213A" authorityName="Hitchc. Contr. U. S. Natl. Herb. 17 (3): 374" authorityYear="1913" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orizabensis">
<emphasis id="D8C39466C9D45DD66B10768728A8490C" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Poa orizabensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens cited).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DDF5E3E22F2DEF90CADD1CC62299E67A" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicName id="FDF7ADBCA2FAEA7A19194182186AB2F6" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruprechtii">
<emphasis id="B5797593736C09C861CA95A73B218041" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Poa ruprechtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
approaches 
<taxonomicName id="48599BDBDEA59B585A822A77D6640002" authorityName="R. W. Pohl" authorityYear="1976" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="talamancae">
<emphasis id="F886E19821C4A004EBFEC4F929CFA644" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Poa talamancae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
R.W. Pohl (Type from Costa Rica, Prov. de Cartago: 83 km from San 
<normalizedToken id="77A11BA70D7182DF05955E720E44ACC3" originalValue="José">Jose</normalizedToken>
on the Pan American Highway, Asuncion (summit of Cerro de la Muerte), open windswept subparamo, 3335 m, 22 Jul 1966, 
<emphasis id="150028BA70A4498C9A3B2E9B60B5506B" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">S.Mori 214 &amp; R.Anderson</emphasis>
(holotype: ISC-324356!; isotypes: LE!, WIS!). However, more study is needed here also.
</paragraph>
